Help us improve FRCDesign.org! We’re looking for beta testers to provide feedback on our stage updates. We are looking for people who have:

  1. Completed stage 1 and are immediately looking to start on stage 2
  2. Have not started the course or are working on stage 1, and are looking to complete up to stage 2 by the end up the month.

If you have completed stage 1, you will immediately be testing the new section of stage 2. If you have not, we will send you a revised version of the stage 2 alpha when you are ready.

We do request that if you are beta testing, you screenshare and vocalize your thought process on Discord (will ensure ypp compliance for students, we will be doing this in a public voice channel). This will help us understand how students progress and interact with the course, and gives you an opportunity to get immediate help/feedback from the course developers themselves.

Your feedback will be used to help guide the development and refinement of the course. As a result, we’ll be immediately implementing changes from your feedback.

Please fill out the google form if you are interested, and if you have any questions, please reply to the post.

If you are interested in alpha testing in a classroom/group setting, please send me a message on Chief Delphi directly.

Thank you!
